        "text": "*[Bug 19088] Fix problem in stats::contrast() documentation*\n<https:\/\/bugs.r-project.org\/show_bug.cgi?id=19088>\n\n--- Comment #7 from Sebastian Meyer (<mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de|seb.meyer@fau.de>) ---\n(In reply to Elin Waring from comment #6)\n&gt; we're talking about failing builds on CRAN\n\nThe referenced 'bayestestR' 0.18.1 gives installation and check warnings (note:\nnot failures) in R 4.5 (\"r-oldrel\") because the package's Rd uses an extended\nsyntax requiring R 4.6.0.\n\n&gt; I looked at a number of md files with `\\linkS4class` and most of them wrap in\n&gt; \\code although not necessarily consistently \n&gt; I guess do that or require a 4.6 minimum to avoid the older CRAN builds.\n\n`\\code{\\linkS4class{XYZ}}` is not an issue. What is new in R 4.6.0 is the\noptional argument in `\\linkS4class[PKG]{XYZ}`; this Rd code fails to parse in R\n&lt; 4.6.0. From the NEWS item: \"Packages with the new syntax need to formally\ndepend on 'R &gt;= 4.6.0'\".\n\n&gt; &lt;code&gt;&lt;a href=\"..\/..\/Matrix\/help\/dgCMatrix-class.html\"&gt;dgCMatrix&lt;\/a&gt;&lt;\/code&gt;\n&gt; \n&gt; CRAN does not like having the &lt;code&gt;&lt;\/code&gt; tag _outside_ of the &lt;a&gt;&lt;\/a&gt;\n&gt; because it is poorly formed HTML.\n\nAFAICS, this is valid HTML, so I'd be surprised if \"CRAN does not like\".\n\nIf anything remains unclear, it will be better to ask for advice elsewhere.",
