                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\n--- Comment #7 from Sebastian Meyer ("
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "mailto:seb.meyer@fau.de",
                                "text": "seb.meyer@fau.de"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": ") ---\n(In reply to Elin Waring from comment #6)"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "we're talking about failing builds on CRAN"
                            }
                        ],
                        "contains_padding": true
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nThe referenced 'bayestestR' 0.18.1 gives installation and check warnings (note:\nnot failures) in R 4.5 (\"r-oldrel\") because the package's Rd uses an extended\nsyntax requiring R 4.6.0.\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "I looked at a number of md files with "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\\linkS4class",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " and most of them wrap in\n \\code although not necessarily consistently \n I guess do that or require a 4.6 minimum to avoid the older CRAN builds."
                            }
                        ],
                        "contains_padding": true
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\n"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\\code{\\linkS4class{XYZ}}",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " is not an issue. What is new in R 4.6.0 is the\noptional argument in "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\\linkS4class[PKG]{XYZ}",
                                "style": {
                                    "code": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "; this Rd code fails to parse in R\n< 4.6.0. From the NEWS item: \"Packages with the new syntax need to formally\ndepend on 'R >= 4.6.0'\".\n\n> <code><a href=\"..\/..\/Matrix\/help\/dgCMatrix-class.html\">dgCMatrix<\/a><\/code>"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n CRAN does not like having the <code><\/code> tag "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "outside",
                                "style": {
                                    "italic": true
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " of the <a><\/a>\n because it is poorly formed HTML."
                            }
                        ],
                        "contains_padding": true
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "\n\nAFAICS, this is valid HTML, so I'd be surprised if \"CRAN does not like\".\n\nIf anything remains unclear, it will be better to ask for advice elsewhere."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
